    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Identify the order of reactivity of halogens towards alkanes.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{I}_2>\\mathrm{Br}_2>\\mathrm{Cl}_2>\\mathrm{F}_2$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{Br}_2>\\mathrm{Cl}_2>\\mathrm{F}_2>\\mathrm{I}_2$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{F}_2>\\mathrm{Cl}_2>\\mathrm{Br}_2>\\mathrm{I}_2$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>$\\quad \\mathrm{Cl}_2>\\mathrm{F}_2>\\mathrm{I}_2>\\mathrm{Br}_2$</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The halogenation of alkanes (free radical substitution) follows the order of ease of reaction (reactivity) among halogens as:</p>\n<p>$ \\mathrm{F}_2 > \\mathrm{Cl}_2 > \\mathrm{Br}_2 > \\mathrm{I}_2 $</p>\n<p><strong>Reasoning:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>The reaction proceeds through a free radical chain mechanism (initiation, propagation, termination).  </p></li>\n<li><p>The key step is the formation of halogen radicals and their reaction with alkyl radicals to form alkyl halides.  </p></li>\n<li><p>The overall energy change (and rate) depends on the <strong>bond dissociation energies</strong> and the stability of the radicals formed:</p></li>\n<li><p>$ \\mathrm{F–F} $ bond is weak, and the reaction with alkanes is <strong>very exothermic and violent</strong>.</p></li>\n<li><p>$ \\mathrm{Cl–Cl} $ reacts readily but controllably.</p></li>\n<li><p>$ \\mathrm{Br–Br} $ reacts slowly and requires heating or light.</p></li>\n<li><p>$ \\mathrm{I–I} $ practically does not react because the reaction is endothermic.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>✅ <strong>Correct option:</strong></p>\n<p>$ \\boxed{\\text{Option C: } \\mathrm{F}_2 > \\mathrm{Cl}_2 > \\mathrm{Br}_2 > \\mathrm{I}_2} $</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2025-9th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
